The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Bomb scare at Bachchan bungalow

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, July 4: The city polices bomb squad today searched Amitabh Bachchans bungalow for possible explosives following an email threatening an attack.

 The house was evacuated and the hunt continued for an hour this afternoon, but nothing could be found.

 The bomb detection and disposal squad, accompanied by sniffer dogs, arrived at Jalsa, in Juhu, after a news channel received the email around 12.55 this afternoon.

 The subject of the email, sent from Appuyadab_ffffyahoo.com, was: pre-planned bomb in Amitabhs bangla. 

 The sender identified himself as Pappu Yadav and claimed to have planted the bomb, which was timed to explode at 4.30pm. The channel forwarded the email to Mumbai police.

 I and Abhishek-Aishwarya were present in the house. Jayaji had gone out. They evacuated the bungalow, and after the search they said everything was fine, Bachchan told reporters.

 Asked if he thought it was a prank played by a fan, the actor said it was up to the police to find out. Bachchan enjoys X-category security cover.




